text:
Little bit of personal connection to this song:
So in my middle school, which was 5th through 7th, you were required to have one music class every year for any given semester. And for the example in this story, I'm gonna talk about my 7th grade year in which I had music class first period for the first semester (from August to December). However at the time (and still now haha), our school district had staffing problems when it came to teachers, so my "music teacher" for that first period music class was one of the assistant principals from the junior high school (which was 8th and 9th grade). Because of that, we never did any actual music class work. All we did was watch funny cat compilations and sing karaoke in class. It was pretty much like I had another study hall, that's how laxed it was in there. But anyways, I remember there was this girl in my class named Jada who LOVED Adele, and every single day without doubt she would sing this song once so long as she had the chance. And she did it in such a memorable way that everytime I hear this song or think about this song, I hear her voice singing it. I don't even mean to, I was never friends with her and she was never important to me, yet I still just think of those days whenever I hear this song. Shivering in the cold classroom, dreading going to second period math, wishing I was at home right then playing San Andreas. It's a very weird feeling to know when I was young, I only ever wanted for the day to end and for time to pass by. But now that it's happened I want nothing more than to just go back in time to 7th grade and be a kid again.

text:
"Someone like You" is a song recorded by English singer-songwriter Adele. It was written a

nd produced by Adele and Dan Wilson for her second studio album, 21 (2011). It is the second single and final track on the album. The song was inspired by a broken relationship with one's life partner, and lyrically speaks of Adele's coming to terms with it. 


XL Recordings released the song as the second single from the album on 24 January 2011 (the same day the album was released) in the United Kingdom and on 9 August 2011 in the United States. Accompanied only by a piano in the song (played by co-writer Wilson), Adele sings about the end of the relationship with her ex-partner.
